# Supabase Article Registration

## When to Use

- Registering new PPL/CPL lesson articles to `learning_contents` table for viewing in the app
- After creating or updating MDX files in `src/content/lessons/`

## Supabase MCP

Use **Supabase MCP** (`my_supabase_project` server) when available:

1. **execute_sql** tool:
   - `project_id`: `fstynltdfdetpyvbrswr` (FlightAcademy project)
   - `query`: SQL for INSERT/UPDATE

2. **Example** (upsert article):
```sql
INSERT INTO learning_contents (id, title, category, sub_category, description, order_index, parent_id, content_type, is_published, updated_at)
VALUES ('PPL-1-1-9_FlightPerformance', '【航空工学】余剰馬力の美学...', 'PPL', '航空工学', '...', 9, NULL, 'text', true, NOW())
ON CONFLICT (id) DO UPDATE SET title = EXCLUDED.title, sub_category = EXCLUDED.sub_category, description = EXCLUDED.description, order_index = EXCLUDED.order_index, content_type = EXCLUDED.content_type, is_published = EXCLUDED.is_published, updated_at = EXCLUDED.updated_at;
```

## Fallback: Node Script

If Supabase MCP is unavailable, use:
```bash
node scripts/database/register_ppl_article.mjs PPL-1-1-9_FlightPerformance
```
Requires `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in `.env.local` (anon key has no write permission).

## Fallback: SQL File

Run `scripts/database/insert_ppl_1_1_9.sql` via Supabase Dashboard SQL Editor.

## learning_contents Schema

| Column | PPL | CPL |
|--------|-----|-----|
| id | filename (e.g. PPL-1-1-9_FlightPerformance) | filename |
| category | PPL | CPL |
| sub_category | 航空工学, 航空気象, etc. | subject name |
| content_type | text | text |
| is_published | true | true |
